Tools: 

- [ uptime ]			# shows for how much time system is/was up
- Again we can use stress here.

For to monitor disk I/O we can use a tool which is [ iotop ]

- we can put some stress on disk using
$ sudo stress --hhd 1 

- we will install one more pkg [ sysstat ]
$ sudo apt-get install sysstat
$ man iostat

- There is one more tool name sar 
$ sar 1 5 

- we can also make use lsof command
$ lsof | grep "stress"
